FBIS4-1602 "drchi063_i_94005" FBIS-CHI-94-063 Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 East Europe Romania To Establish `Permanent Presence' in Guangdong Romania To Establish `Permanent Presence' in Guangdong HK1503011694 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1350 GMT 14 Mar 94 HK1503011694 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE English BFN [Text] Guangzhou, March 14 (CNS) -- Romanian President Mr. Ion Iliescu said today during his visit to Guangdong that Romania would establish a permanent presence in the province to strengthen cooperation between China and Romania. The president and his party left for Romania this afternoon after a four-day visit to Shenzhen, Zhuhai and Guangzhou. Vice Governor of Guangdong Mr. Lu Ruihua met the Romanian party last night. He gave an account of the province's recent economic development and said he welcomed Romanian investment and cooperation in the province. Mr. Iliescu said he was very glad to see Guangdong's economic achievements and that Romania planned to set up a permanent presence there to strengthen exchange and cooperation with China.
